the basis of threshold cost-effectiveness values used in the NHS and subject to 
a delay of up to about 80 minutes. These findings are mainly explained by the 
superior mortality benefit and the prevention of non-fatal outcomes associated 
with primary angioplasty for delays of up to this length.

